L2-boosting with caret: Boston dataset

Load libraries

rm(list=ls())
library(MASS)
library(caret)

Create data partition

set.seed(123)
split <- createDataPartition(y=Boston$medv, p = 0.7, list=FALSE)

train <- Boston[split,]
nrow(train)
## [1] 356
test = Boston[-split,-14]
test.y = Boston[-split,14]
nrow(test)
## [1] 150

Cross-validation settings

cv <- trainControl(
  method = "repeatedcv",
  number = 5,
  repeats = 2
)

Models

rf <- train(
  medv~., train,
  method = "rf",
  trControl=cv)

grid <- expand.grid(
  n.trees = c(500, 1000, 1500),
  shrinkage = c(0.01, 0.05),
  interaction.depth = c(2,4,5,6), 
  n.minobsinnode = c(5,10)
)
boost <- train(
  medv~., train,
  method = "gbm",
  tuneGrid = grid,
  verbose = FALSE,
  trControl=cv)

plot(boost)

boost$bestTune
##    n.trees interaction.depth shrinkage n.minobsinnode
## 21    1500                 6      0.01              5

Cross-validation RMSE

models = list(
    rf=rf,
    boost=boost
  )

resamps = resamples(models)
bwplot(resamps, metric = "RMSE")

Test RMSE

yhats = predict(models, newdata=test)
lapply(yhats, function(yhat) sqrt( mean( (yhat - test.y)^2) ) )
## $rf
## [1] 4.062246
## 
## $boost
## [1] 3.47906
predVals <- extractPrediction(models, 
                              testX = test, 
                              testY = test.y)

plotObsVsPred(predVals)
